    "body": "### Problem\n\nI use following code to update check highlit, but failed\n\n```lua\n  if\n    vim.api.nvim_get_hl(0, { name = config.config.highlights.title })\n    == vim.empty_dict()\n  then\n    vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, config.config.highlights.title, {\n      fg = normal.bg,\n      bg = normal.fg,\n      bold = true,\n    })\n  end\n```\n\nThis is because if the hight does not exist, nvim_get_hl return vim.empty_dict(), and vim.empty_dict() == vim.empty_dict() = fasle\n\nI think this should be true.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n\n```\n  if\n    vim.empty_dict()\n    == vim.empty_dict()\n  then\n    print(1)\n  end\n```\n\nnow I need to change it to:\n\n```lua\n  if\n    vim.tbl_isempty(vim.api.nvim_get_hl(0, { name = config.config.highlights.title }))\n  then\n    vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, config.config.highlights.title, {\n      fg = normal.bg,\n      bg = normal.fg,\n      bold = true,\n    })\n  end\n\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n:=vim.empty_dict() == vim.empty_dict() return true\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nnvim v0.1.4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nwin 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nweztem\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nscoop install neovim",
